text.tspan: Differences in life expectancy are more regional than national,
Life expectancy at birth indicates the number of years a newborn infant would live if prevailing patterns of mortality at the time of its
birth were to stay the same throughout its life.
Data source: United Nations Population Division and others (via World Bank)
